thy Memorial Scholarship\n# Mr. Chavali Ambika Sankar Memorial Scholarship\n# Gummuluri Satyanarayana Memorial Scholarship\n# B. Lalithamba, B. Sarojini Memorial Scholarship\n#  Vadlamani Venkata Rao Memorial Scholarship\n# C. P. S. Teja Memorial Scholarship\n# Sri K. S. N. Sarma  Memorial Scholarship\n# Smt. Mallajosyula Suridamma Award\n# Dr. A. V. D. Sarma Award\n# Upmaka Narasimha Murthy Memorial Scholarship\n# Poodipeddi Suryanarayana Memorial Scholarship\n# Prof. E. S. Murthy and Smt. E. Nagamamba Memorial Scholarship\n# Prof. E. Venkata Rao Endowment Scholarship\n# Haji Md. Badshah Saheb Memorial Scholarship\n# Sri Bh. S. Krishna Murthy Memorial Merit Scholarship\n# Duvvuri Venkateswara Rao Memorial Scholarship\n# Duvvuri Sri Rama Lakshmi Narasimha Rao Memorial Scholarship\n# Duvvuri Atchyuta Anantha Satyanarayana Memorial Scholarship\n# Vallabhajosyula Madhusudhana Rao Memorial Cash Scholarship\n# The G. S. Bhargava Award\n-->\n\n==Old Students's Association==\n'''Maharajah's College Old Students's Association (MRCOSA)''' has been functioning since the inception of college. Its organized the Maharajah Ananda Gajapati Sapada Sata Jayanti, the 125th Anniversary of Maharajah Ananda Gajapati Raju in 1976. It was revived when the college became Autonomous in 1987. It was made an integral part of the College in 1993.\n\n==Notable alumni==\n[[Alumni]] of the institution are listed alphabetically:\n* Prof. [[Allam Appa Rao]], Vice Chancellor of [[Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University, Kakinada]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://jntuk.edu.in/vcdesk/assets/flash/aar.pdf |title=Biodata of Allam Apparao. |access-date=3 September 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110630234553/http://jntuk.edu.in/vcdesk/assets/flash/aar.pdf |archive-date=30 June 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Dr. [[A. L. Rao]], Chief Operating Officer, [[Wipro]]<ref>[http://www.wiprocorporate.com/pressroom/alrao.asp Dr. A. L. Rao at Wipro Corporate.com]</ref>\n* Prof. [[Beela Satyanarayana]], Vice Chancellor of [[Andhra University]].\n* [[Botsa Satyanarayana]], Indian Parliamentarian.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://164.100.47.132/LssNew/members/former_Biography.aspx?mpsno=62 |title=Botcha Satyanarayana at Lok Sabha |access-date=5 April 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304023040/http://164.100.47.132/LssNew/members/former_Biography.aspx?mpsno=62 |archive-date=4 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Bulusu Sambamurti]], was an Indian lawyer, politician and freedom-fighter\n* [[Chaganti Somayajulu]], Telugu writers.\n* [[Dwaram Bhavanarayana Rao]], musicologist and Principal of [[Maharajah's Government College of Music and Dance]].\n* Dr. D. N. Rao\n* Justice [[E. Venkatesam]], former Judge of [[Andhra Pradesh High Court]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://hc.ap.nic.in/aphc/evj.html |title=Biodata of Justice E. Venkatesam at Andhra Pradesh High Court. |access-date=13 September 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303202254/http://hc.ap.nic.in/aphc/evj.html |archive-date=3 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Justice [[G. Ramanujulu Naidu]], former Judge of [[Andhra Pradesh High Court]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://hc.ap.nic.in/aphc/grnj.html |title=Profile of G. Ramanujulu Naidu at Andhra Pradesh High Court. |access-date=13 September 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150317060433/http://hc.ap.nic.in/aphc/grnj.html |archive-date=17 March 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Ganti Jogi Somayaji]], Telugu scholar and faculty in [[Andhra University]].\n* Ganti Prasada Rao, electrical engineering and systems science scholar, researcher and academician.\n* [[Gidugu Venkata Ramamurthy]], the father of Colloquial Telugu language movement.\n* [[Gurazada Apparao]], poet.\n* [[Indukuri Ramakrishnam Raju]], better known as [[Rajashri]], dialogue and lyrics writer in Telugu cinema.<ref>Rajashri, 20th Century Telugu Luminaries, Part II, Potti Sriramulu Telugu University, Hyderabad, 2005, pp: 481-2.</ref>\n* [[J. V. Somayajulu]], theater and film actor.\n* Justice [[K. Punnayya]], former Judge of [[Andhra Pradesh High Court]] and [[Member of Legislative Assembly]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://hc.ap.nic.in/aphc/kpj.html |title=Profile of K. Punnayya at Andhra Pradesh High Court. |access-date=13 September 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303192503/http://hc.ap.nic.in/aphc/kpj.html |archive-date=3 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Dr. K. S. R. Krishna Rao\n* General [[K. V. Krishna Rao]], former [[Chief of the Army Staff (India)|Chief of the Army Staff]] of the [[Indian Army]].\n* [[Kala Venkata Rao]], freedom fighter and politician.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://dspace.vidyanidhi.org.in:8080/dspace/bitstream/2009/4764/6/AND-1996-041-5.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=18 September 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721183049/http://dspace.vidyanidhi.org.in:8080/dspace/bitstream/2009/4764/6/AND-1996-041-5.pdf |archive-date=21 July 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Kandala Subrahmanyam]], lawyer and [[Member of Parliament]] from Vizianagaram constituency.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://164.100.47.132/LssNew/biodata_1_12/1049.htm |title=Biodata of Shri Kandala Subrahmanyam at Lok Sabha website. |access-date=2 September 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303180818/http://164.100.47.132/LssNew/biodata_1_12/1049.htm |archive-date=3 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Kotcherlakota Rangadhama Rao]], Indian Physicist.\n* [[M. V. Narayana Rao]], Chief of [[Crime Investigation Department (India)|Crime Investigation Department]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cidap.gov.in/htmlfiles/chiefs.html |title=List of CID Chiefs. |access-date=4 September 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101021061811/http://www.cidap.gov.in/htmlfiles/chiefs.html |archive-date=21 October 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[N. Dilip Kumar]], Chief of Anti-Corruption Branch.<ref>[http://indiatoday.intoday.in/site/Story/105619/Cover%20Story/n-dilip-kumar.html]</ref>\n* [[Nyapathi Kameswari]] better known as Radio Akkayya.\n* P. L. N. Raju\n* [[P. V. Ramanaiah Raja]], founder of [[Sri Raja-Lakshmi Foundation]].\n* Major General P. V. Ramanaiah\n* [[Pappu Venugopala Rao]], musicologist.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.pappuvenugopalarao.com/ |title=Official website of Pappu Venugopala Rao |access-date=3 September 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007145518/http://pappuvenugopalarao.com/ |archive-date=7 October 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* Justice [[Penmetsa Satyanarayana Raju]] former [[Chief Justice]] of [[Andhra Pradesh High Court]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://hc.ap.nic.in/aphc/psrj.html |title=Profile of P. Satyanarayana Raju at Andhra Pradesh High Court. |access-date=18 September 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120227061607/http://hc.ap.nic.in/aphc/psrj.html |archive-date=27 February 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Pulapaka Seethapathi Rao]], CEO of [[State Bank of Hyderabad]] during 1965\u201370\n* Prof. (Dr.) Pyla Narayana Rao, Faculty at School of Corporate Law, Indian Institute of Corporate Affairs (IICA), New Delhi.\n* Justice [[T. V. R. Tatachari]], [[Chief Justice]] of [[Delhi High Court]].<ref>[http://delhihighcourt.nic.in/ Biodata of T. V. R. Tatachari at Delhi High Court website.]</ref>\n* V. R. Panthulu\n* [[Vasantha Rao Venkata Rao]], Physics teacher\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n17. Profile of Dr. Pyla Narayana Rao at http://www.iica.in/\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.mracollegevzm.com/ Official website]\n\n{{coord missing|Andhra Pradesh}}\n\n[[Category:Colleges in Andhra Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Vizianagaram district]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1879]]\n[[Category:1879 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Uttarandhra]]\n[[Category:Colleges affiliated to Andhra University]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|text= [[Maharaja's College, Ernakulam]], [[Maharaja's College, Mysore]] or [[Maharaja College, Jaipur]]}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox university\n|name            = Maharajah's College\n|native_name     = '''\u0c2e\u0c39\u0c3e\u0c30\u0c3e\u0c1c\u0c3e \u0c15\u0c33\u0c3e\u0c36\u0c3e\u0c32'''\n|image_name      = Maharaja's College Logo.PNG\n|image_size      =\n|caption         = Logo\n|latin_name      =\n|motto           = Righteousness in the heart and beauty in the character\n|tagline         =\n|established     = 1879\n|type            = Autonomous institution\n|endowment       =\n|staff           =\n|faculty         =\n|president       =\n|provost         =\n|principal       = Dr. M.D.Prasad Patnaik\n|rector          =\n|chancellor      =\n|vice_chancellor =\n|director        =\n|dean            =\n|head_label      = Chairman\n|head            = Sri Pusapati Anand Gajapathi Raju\n|students        =\n|undergrad       = 2,192 per year\n|postgrad        =\n|doctoral        =\n|profess         =\n|city            = [[Vizianagaram]]\n|state           = [[Andhra Pradesh]]\n|country         = [[India]]\n|campus          = Urban\n|free_label      =\n|free            =\n|colors          =\n|colours         =\n|mascot          =\n|fightsong       =\n|nickname        =\n|affiliations    =\n|footnotes       =\n|website         = [http://maharajahscollegevzm.com/]\n|address         = [[Vizianagaram]], [[Andhra Pradesh]], India [[India]]\n|coor            =\n|logo            =\n}}\n'''Maharajah's College''', or '''M. R. College''', ({{te|\u0c2e\u0c39\u0c3e\u0c30\u0c3e\u0c1c\u0c3e \u0c15\u0c33\u0c3e\u0c36\u0c3e\u0c32}}) is one of the oldest [[college]]s in [[India]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://vizianagaram.ap.nic.in/AboutVizianagaram.htm |title=Vizianagaram district Official website. |access-date=30 August 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100826065149/http://vizianagaram.ap.nic.in/AboutVizianagaram.htm |archive-date=26 August 2010 |url-status=dead }}</ref> It was established in 1879 by Sri Poosapati Vijayarama Gajapathi, [[Maharajah of Vizianagram]]. [[National Accreditation and Assessment Council]] (NAAC) assessed and accredited the institution with \"B\" grade.<ref>naacindia.org/EC%20-%2048/52%20Maharajah's%20College,%20AP.doc</ref>\n\nThere are 21 departments offering 19 undergraduate and postgraduate courses. There are about 150 permanent and temporary academic and support staff members with an annual intake of about 2,192 students in 2009.\n\n==Profile==\nThe institution was founded by Sri Pusapati Vijayarama Gajapathi Raju, the [[Maharajah of Vizianagram]]. It was started as a middle school in 1857 and upgraded to a high school in 1868. It was upgraded to a college in 1879. Graduation classes were started in 1881 under the patronage of Sri [[Pusapati Ananda Gajapati Raju]]. The Rajah Saheb [[P. V. G. Raju]] gifted the Royal Palace to the college in 1948. The [[MANSAS]] (Maharajah Alak Narayan Society of Arts and Sciences) came into existence in 1958. Dr. P. V. G. Raju died on 13 November 1995. His son Dr. Pusapati Ananda Gajapathi Raju has taken charge as Chairman and Pusapati Ashok Gajapathi Raju is the Vice-Chairman. Autonomous status was conferred on the college in 1987.\n\n==Principals==\nFor a list of [[Principal (academia)|Principal]]s, see the end of this article.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Name of the Principal !! Term begins !! Term ends\n|-\n| Sri C. Chandra Sekhara Sastry || 1879 || 1887\n|-\n| Dr. [[K. Ramanujachari]] || 1887 || 1920\n|-\n| Sri Y. Narasimham || 1920 || 1922\n|-\n| Sri K. Janaki Rao || 1922 || 1934\n|-\n| Sri U. Subbaraya Bhat || 1934 || 1939\n|-\n| Sri S. Purushottam || 1939 || 1945\n|-\n| Dr. K. R. Subrahmaniam || 1945 || 1948\n|-\n| Dr. [[A. L. Narayan]] || 1948 || 1956\n|-\n| Sri [[V. Venkata Rao]] || 1956 || 1962\n|-\n| Dr. N. Ramlal || 1962 || 1963\n|-\n| Sri [[V. Venkata Rao]] || 1963 || 1969\n|-\n| Sri. V. Linga Murthy || 1969 || 1976\n|-\n| Sri D. L. Satyanarayana || 1976 || 1985\n|-\n| Sri. P. B. V. Raju || 1985 || 1986\n|-\n| Sri K. Suresh Kumar || 1986 || 1987\n|-\n| Sri M. V. Jagannadha Rao || 1987 || 1988\n|-\n| Sri P. B. V. Raju || 1988 || 1990\n|-\n| Sri G. V. R. Subrahmaniam || 1990 || 1993\n|-\n| Dr. C. Madan Mohan Rao || 1993 || 1994\n|-\n| Sri K. Ranga Rao || 1994 || 1996\n|-\n| Sri. P. V. Sainadha Sastry || 1996 || 1997\n|-\n| Sri P. Nagaraju || 1998 || 1998\n|-\n| Dr. D. B. Subba Rao || 1998 || 2001\n|-\n| Sri G. V. Suryanarayana || 2001 || 2003\n|-\n| Dr. K. Subrahmanyam || 2003 || 2004\n|-\n| Dr. A. Raghava Rao || 2004 || 2004\n|-\n| Sri K. Atchuta Rao || 2004 || 2005\n|-\n| Dr. A. Raghava Rao || 2005 || 2006\n|-\n| Dr. A. V. D. Sarma || 2006 || 2008\n|-\n| Sri M. V. Prabhakara Rao || 2008 || 2008\n|-\n| Dr. D. R. K. Raju || 2008 || 2011\n|-\n| Dr. Bh. Subrahmanyam || 2011 || 2012\n|-\n|Dr. M. D. Prasad Patnaik || 2012 || 2013\n|-\n|Dr. L. Ravi Kumar || 2013 || 2015\n|-\n|Dr.G.A.Kalyani || 2015 || Still\n|}\n\n==Infrastructure==\nThe Maharajah's College is spread over 18 acres, hosting six buildings with a construction area of {{convert|115307|sqft|m2|abbr=on}}. There are 51 class rooms, 21 laboratories and 10 staff rooms. There is a central library and 14 other departmental libraries. The central library hasn 50,00 books, and 20 computers connected to the Internet. There are two seminar halls and a Health centre. There is a boys hostel in the campus. There is a playground with facilities for volleyball, basketball, Kabaddi, Kho-Kho, ball badminton, tennis, cricket, football and hockey. There are facilities for indoor games and a gymnasium. There is [[Andhra Bank]] branch in campus serving the needs of the staff and students.\n\n==Academics==\n\n===Departments===\n*  Department of [[Agriculture]]\n*  Department of [[Botany]]\n*  Department of [[Chemistry]]\n*  Department of [[Commerce]]\n*  Department of [[Economics]]\n*  Department of [[English language|English]]\n*  Department of [[Geography]]\n*  Department of [[Geology]]\n*  Department of [[Hindi]]\n*  Department of [[History]]\n*  Department of [[Industrial Relations]]\n*  Department of [[Mathematics]]\n*  Department of [[Philosophy]]\n*  Department of [[Physics]]\n*  Department of [[Politics]]\n*  Department of [[Sanskrit]]\n*  Department of [[Social Work]]\n*  Department of [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n*  Department of [[Zoology]]\n*  Department of [[Library]] and [[Information Science]]\n*  Department of [[Physical Education]]\n\n===Courses===\n* '''Intermediate Course'''\n** Biology, Physics and Chemistry\n** Commerce, Economics and Civics\n** Geography, Economics and Commerce\n** Geology, Physics and Chemistry\n** History, Civics and Special Telugu\n** History, Economics and Civics\n** Logic, Economics and Commerce\n** Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry\n* '''Diploma in Computer Skills'''\n* '''Diploma in Tally Accounting Executive Course'''\n* '''Bachelor of Arts'''\n** Economics, Politics and Philosophy\n** History, Economics and Politics\n** Industrial Relations, Economics and Politics\n** Social Work, Economics and Politics\n** Telugu, History and Politics\n* '''Bachelor of Business Management'''\n* '''Bachelor of Commerce'''\n* '''Bachelor of Science'''\n** Botany, Agriculture and Chemistry\n** Botany, Zoology and Chemistry\n** Geology, Physics and Chemistry\n** Mathematics, Physics and Chemistry\n** Mathematics, Physics and Geology\n** Mathematics, Physics and Statistics\n** Zoology, Agriculture and Chemistry\n* '''Master of Science''' in Analytical Chemistry, Electronics, Organic Chemistry, Physics\n\n<!--APOLOGIES TO WHOEVER TYPED THE NEXT SECTION BUT IT IS WAY TOO LONG AND LOOKS VERY ODD IN THE ARTICLE. I HAD TO TAKE IT OUT. \n==Scholarships, Prizes and Medals==\nThere are about 117 Scholarships, Prizes and Medals given annually to meritorious students in different subjects.\n# Sri Maremanda Narasinga Rao Memorial Scholarship\n# Dr. Ramanujachari Scholarship\n# Sri [[Chatti Purnayya Pantulu]] Memorial Scholarship\n# Maturu China Sanyasilingam and Maturu Venkata Ratnam Prizes\n# Smt. Alaka Rajeswari S